text:
today is 9 years since my first operation for endometrosis and so 9 years since my official diagnosis. 
i had been ignored long enough by doctors to have 2 endometriomas - one the size of a large new born baby and one the size of a grapefruit. it was too severe for keyhole surgery.

i'd found a lump in the november before. that was two months after a person who i cared for deeply violated me in the most intimate and violent of ways and so i thought i might be pregnant. i wasn't. the night before my operation this same person popped up on msn to tell me why i had deserved it. 
what with the rape and the operation (not linked but intertwined forever in my mind) those 4 months changed everything forever.

i don't know how i did it. i look back at that time and at who i was and i want to bundle her up and take that blow for her. but i did it. i adapted, i overcame, i evolved. it took a lot of time and energy i didn't always have. 
but i did it. and here i am now! 9 years later. stronger than ever, doing something i love, surrounded by the most incredible people. it was hard to see how life could end up like this, how i could ever be happy. but i am. 
if you're a victim of any of this i want you to know you have the strength. my inbox is always there for you. you can do this. i love you 💛
#9yearslater #endometriosis #endowarrior #surgery #chronicillness #spoonie #metoo #survivor #cptsd #depression #anxiety #mentalhealth

text:
föreläsning 13/3 på oskarshamns folkhögskola med etikläraren torbjörn helmner. i sin föreläsning berör han etiska ställningstaganden och perspektiv på människovärdet som aktualiserats i ljuset av #metoo.
hur kan vi skapa ett samhälle som bygger på förväntningar, tillit och förtroende istället för rädsla, misstro och fiendskap? torbjörn presenterar olika historiska värdeuppfattningar, etiska dilemman och lyfter fram hur etiska riktlinjer fungerar som ett sammanhållande kitt i ett mångkulturellt samhälle.

torbjörn helmner är etiklärare på nova utbildning, forskning & affärsutveckling. master of theology med inriktning etik. författare till boken ”gud som metafor”. onsdag 13/3 kl. 18.30-20.00
lokal: utsikten på oskarshamns folkhögskola

boka plats: 0491-768 104 eller via mejl: info@oskarshamnsfolkhogskola.se

föreläsningen är kostnadsfri, välkommen!

text:
✅ oggi ,vi presentiamo il mese di febbraio del calendario delle guerriere:sciences arts&events. 🎬 foto scattata da @lucamengonifoto per @dececco.federica @monica.melone5 @eva.sch76 nella suggestiva location di marina dorica ancona. un doveroso ringraziamento va ai fantastici bodypainters  valeria amatiello @alaydespernanzoni @yurifalzetti e al nostro amico @andrea.cleanpeak per la realizzazione del calendario.
vi lasciamo alcune curiosita’🤓riguardante questo mese. 👉🏻il nome febbraio deriva dal latino “februare”, che significa “purificare” o “rimediare agli errori” dato che nel calendario romano febbraio era il periodo dei rituali di purificazione, tenuti in onore del dio etrusco februus e della dea romana febris, i quali avevano il loro clou il giorno 14. tale ricorrenza pagana sembrerebbe poi essere confluita nel culto cristiano tributato in onore a santa febronia, poi soppiantata da san valentino. “chi vive sempre nel calore e nella pienezza del cuore e per così dire nell’aria estiva dell’anima, non può immaginarsi il misterioso rapimento che afferra le nature più invernali, che vengono eccezionalmente toccate dai raggi dell’amore e dal tiepido soffio di un solatio giorno di febbraio.
(friedrich nietzsche)”
🍀#vivalavita #artecura #cancerawarness #metoo #breastcancerfighter #cancersurvivor #cancroalseno #tumorealseno #tumore #oncologia #leguerrieresciencesartsandevents

vi lasciamo alcune curiosita’🤓riguardante questo mese. 👉🏻il nome febbraio deriva dal latino “februare”, che significa “purificare” o “rimediare agli errori” dato che nel calendario romano febbraio era il periodo dei rituali di purificazione, tenuti in onore del dio etrusco februus e della dea romana febris, i quali avevano il loro clou il giorno 14. tale ricorrenza pagana sembrerebbe poi essere confluita nel culto cristiano tributato in onore a santa febronia, poi soppiantata da san valentino. “chi vive sempre nel calore e nella pienezza del cuore e per così dire nell’aria estiva dell’anima, non può immaginarsi il misterioso rapimento che afferra le nature più invernali, che vengono eccezionalmente toccate dai raggi dell’amore e dal tiepido soffio di un solatio giorno di febbraio.
(friedrich nietzsche)”
🍀

hello february! happy first day of the month!! i love a new month, you get fresh start with a new month. what will you do different this month to continue working towards your yearly goals? one thing i want to do this month is to get better organized. now don’t get me wrong, i’m pretty organized but since we are moving it’s time to take it to the next level. i’m going to go on an organize spree. i want to get more organized for work, my side business and my personal space. i’ll be keeping you updated. be sure to watch my stories. .
.

.
.

text:
this is mary broderick. my maternal grandmother. she was a legit beauty queen 💯👸🏻 she was 20 years old when she won the title of miss south australia in adelaide during september in 1931. she was also winner of many surf girl competitions in her teens, a time where women were slandered and bullied for being overtly sexual and inappropriate and well downright dangerous. my guess is she too would’ve been part of the #metoo movement, being a swimsuit model and all during the 20’s & 30’s. she retired when my uncle & mother we’re born in the 1940’s. sadly, she then died riddled with breast cancer at the age of 44 in 1956. my mum was 8. my mother was then diagnosed with breast cancer at 50 and subsequently died of lung cancer or secondary breast cancer at the age of 67, and but that’s another story for another time for another time.

so, why am i writing this post you ask? well i’m 46, and i’m in a bracket of 1 in 4 women, more than likely to get breast cancer at sometime in my life cause...genetics. i have bi yearly mammograms and had my last one last week and the results came back today. and this time....they’re clear 🙏 but i want to say to all women, in fact emplore to all women to check your boobs everyday. make sure you book those mammograms every couple of years. instagramming your boobs may be fun but having breast cancer from what i can see and have experienced vicariously through family & friends isn’t  fucking fun at all. i want to express my utter respect, to all the women that have breast cancer or have had breast cancer. in fact if i could help any of you,  i would come round and do that right now!!!!! look after your boobs, and remind your sisters to do this too. cancer absolutely fucking sucks. 
thank you @breastscreenvictoria for treating me and my boobs so wonderfully 🙏 i pray i don’t have to see you again (in a good way) till 2021 💞💞💞💞 #worldcancerday #fuckcancer #breastcancerawareness
#checkyourboobs

so, why am i writing this post you ask? well i’m 46, and i’m in a bracket of 1 in 4 women, more than likely to get breast cancer at sometime in my life cause...genetics. i have bi yearly mammograms and had my last one last week and the results came back today. and this time....they’re clear 🙏 but i want to say to all women, in fact emplore to all women to check your boobs everyday. make sure you book those mammograms every couple of years. instagramming your boobs may be fun but having breast cancer from what i can see and have experienced vicariously through family & friends isn’t  fucking fun at all. i want to express my utter respect, to all the women that have breast cancer or have had breast cancer. in fact if i could help any of you,  i would come round and do that right now!!!!! look after your boobs, and remind your sisters to do this too. cancer absolutely fucking sucks. 
thank you  for treating me and my boobs so wonderfully 🙏 i pray i don’t have to see you again (in a good way) till 2021 💞💞💞💞   reastcancerawareness

text: it's women like fiona, frida and esther who further inspire me to want to help the women of @wacwausoap take the next steps in the development of their business in uganda. not part of the initial group of women to participate in the first training with me, we have invited two of them to join the cooperative and are committing ongoing support to another and her farming activities. fiona, a headmistress once at a local school until lack of funding forced its closure, was then beaten and attacked with a knife by her husband and then abandoned with their children. men often marry women with albinism and then expect them to be good luck charms and bring them wealth. if that then doesn't happen, they often abuse and discard them. and then there is frida, a mother of four children with albinism. she is a farmer who grows cassava and groundnuts, she barely gets by. her husband also abandoned all of them but then over the years has tried to have his own children kidnapped and sold for their body parts.  esther, a woman with two children, has experienced something recently at the hands of a horrible man and is now struggling to rebuild her life.  these are just three women's stories.there are 30 of them who will be a part of this business. all of them have similar stories to tell. with the growth of this business, we will also be able to give opportunities to other women affected by albinism. i leave for uganda again on february 21st. we have raised a combined total of £996 across three fundraising platforms and we need £2000 to launch a cooperatively-owned business for these thirty women. the @gofundme link can be find in my profile. please read it and invest in these women with me if you can. feel free to also share 💕 photo credits text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
amaal malik slams uncle anu malik; sona mohapatra labels him as a trauma

recently, the #metoo wave took the bollywood industry by storm and many renowned names came under scanner in this movement. amongst all, there was singer anu malik’s name too and singers like sona mohapatra and shweta pandit accused him of sexual misconduct.

now, singer amaal malik, who is one the family members of anu malik, has come out in open and spoken about the allegations against him.
amaal malik slams uncle anu malik; sona mohapatra labels him as a trauma
amaal malik slams uncle anu malik; sona mohapatra labels him as a trauma

in a recent interview, amaal was asked about the #metoo controversy on his uncle anu, to which he said that he doesn’t consider him as a family. he said, “when it happened, it is obviously a little humiliating. but, more importantly, i would like to say that my family is first my four people. beyond that, i don’t count anyone as a family. unki apni family (he has his own family) hai and it was a tough time for them.” reacting to this, sona took to her twitter and wrote, “having anu malik as an uncle must be trauma enough & no fault of yours & then sonu bhaiya has confused u impressionable minds enough about courts being the only ones who can/should curb sexual predators.not true, @amaalmallik , we all have a duty to call out & curb such menace. 1”  having anu malik as an uncle must be trauma enough & no fault of yours & then sonu bhaiya has confused u impressionable minds enough about courts being the only ones who can/should curb sexual predators.not true, @amaalmallik , we all have a duty to call out & curb such menace.  he further also said that he supports the #metoo movement. he said, “i support the movement and i’m completely with it. what happens is, when people talk on social media, it goes a little wrong. when you have alleged someone and taken their name, you should drag it to the court and through the judicial system, try to achieve what you want to achieve. because if you don’t take it ahead then why did you even do this in the first place.”

text:
протеиновый батончик energy pro содержит все необходимое для эффективной силовой тренировки.
28% качественного белка
дополнительный белок в составе – растительный. орехи содержат большое количество белка, необходимого при интенсивных тренировках и наращивании мышечной массы. еще в них есть важная аминокислота – аргинин, которая способствует выработке гормона роста и полезна при наращивании мышечной массы. кроме того, аргинин необходим для вырабатывания креатина – вещества, которое является первостепенным источником энергии для мышц.
900 мг всаа для роста и лучшего восстановления мышц после каждой тренировки.
креатин помогает увеличивать силовые показатели при работе на рельеф.
14 витаминов и минералов «работают» на максимальный эффект от употребления батончиков.
для кого?
для тех, кто хочет добавить белка в свое меню.
для тех, кто занимается спортом.
для тех, кто хочет вкусно и c пользой перекусить.
для тех, кто хочет стать более выносливым и сильным.

text_retweet:
reposted from @muslimahnewsid - / perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks /
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.”
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
“menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
——

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.”
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
“menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
——

text:
linda vista. when hollyweed leaks onto the stage...
yesterday i saw a play. it was ridiculous.
..how should i put it? 🤔
a modern play about stupidity and misery with the elements of political humour and porn.* plus, with mostly old people in the audience.
i feel sorry for all the play’s characters...
the play is written by tracy letts after the events of #metoo movement. i guess, the idea was to show strong and independent women who dump the main character.

text:
“in the depth of winter, i finally learned that within me there lay an invincible summer.” albert camus
.
in therapy i learned something fascinating about childhood trauma. often, as children, we can’t process the negative feelings and emotions that accompany the terrible things that are happening to us. as a result, we shove them far away in the back of our brain! but our brain is smart. it knows it’s not healthy to keep those there. so as you grow older, your brain subconsciously recognizes when you’re ready to work through these terribly hard emotions and feelings. it pulls a fast one on you and starts creeping those feelings to the surface.
.
hello! can we say no thank you? yup, pretty sure i still don’t want to deal with it. but this time, they’re not going away. in a frustrated effort to keep these feelings and emotions in check, adults will often turn to substance abuse, immorality and suicide. not to mention the unhealthy approach they bring to relationships.
.
so while in therapy, my therapist asked me how my abuse made me feel. i looked at him, dumbfounded. “oh no, it didn’t! i don’t really feel anything.” i told him. lies! so he gave me an assignment, to write down everything i could remember about my abuse.
.
i was immediately uncomfortable and i remember asking him why that was necessary. it seemed totally unproductive to me. his answer scared me!
.
because, if you can’t recognize how it made you feel, then i can’t help you overcome those feelings. and if you never overcome those feelings, you’re bound to make the same choices all over again.
.
okay! okay! i’ll write it down!
.
as i shared all of this with a friend at lunch today she shared with me that she has some things from her past that she has tucked away. but she doesn’t want to get vulnerable and work through it. i lovingly punched her on the arm and encouraged her to go after it.
.
you guys, get vulnerable! dig in! do the hard work! even it means digging into the past. life is meant to be enjoyed, not just endured.
.
create something of your life that is real! that you love! you’ve got an adventure waiting for you. don’t wait another second to start it. #asoulsurvivorspiritual

text:
i grew up in a home where i was compared to an older brother who fell in line and was more relatable to my father. my father was upfront about his displeasure with me from as early as i can remember. i fought like hell to gain his approval, but walked away each time, unsuccessful.
.
there is a lot of conflict in our culture about #toxicmasculinity and the #boyswillbeboys culture. i think much of the issues continue to scoot around other issues. there are new categories of what is what, how to be pc, and nowhere to go with your confusion/questions and not be attacked for expressing curiosity.
.
here is what i will say:  i wish the lines between masculine and feminine were not so distinct. i wish instead of battling male and female, we graciously addressed human and inhumane.  i believe the issues at hand have affected both sexes, and all races for as long as history has existed.
.
do i believe black females have gotten the brunt of the most horrific prejudice? yes, i do. i believe that, because i am aware of facts and history. do i believe gay people have been murdered and tortured for being gay? yes, i do, because that is factual. do i believe the white male has been privileged in ways that others have not? yes, i do. i believe that because although i have not had a privileged upbringing, i have been catered to in ways, that dismissed females.
.
i am not looking to rally debates. i am simply saying:  i look forward to the day where someone speaks up about harm done to them, and we see a soul needing help. we see harm needing healing, and we act according to that fire in our gut that craves humanity knowing its value.
.
the greatest gift i have received from overcoming trauma is celebrating that although i grew up in an environment that tried to beat me in to the mold they preferred, i fought like hell to overcome that, and my gentle heart remains… i love being exposed to the scary stuff. traveling to the unknown, opening up your mind and heart to see anew, and finding there… so many broken hearts who are looking to be loved. all shapes. all colors. all sexes… all wounded… my hope is that we pay attention to the broken and be a place to rebuild…

do i believe black females have gotten the brunt of the most horrific prejudice? yes, i do. i believe that, because i am aware of facts and history. do i believe gay people have been murdered and tortured for being gay? yes, i do, because that is factual. do i believe the white male has been privileged in ways that others have not? yes, i do. i believe that because although i have not had a privileged upbringing, i have been catered to in ways, that dismissed females.
.
i am not looking to rally debates. i am simply saying:  i look forward to the day where someone speaks up about harm done to them, and we see a soul needing help. we see harm needing healing, and we act according to that fire in our gut that craves humanity knowing its value.
.
the greatest gift i have received from overcoming trauma is celebrating that although i grew up in an environment that tried to beat me in to the mold they preferred, i fought like hell to overcome that, and my gentle heart remains… i love being exposed to the scary stuff. traveling to the unknown, opening up your mind and heart to see anew, and finding there… so many broken hearts who are looking to be loved. all shapes. all colors. all sexes… all wounded… my hope is that we pay attention to the broken and be a place to rebuild…

omg storytime: so a few months ago i was walking down a side-street alone at about 1:30pm to get to an appointment with my therapist and a car with two adult tradies (construction workers) slows down to follow me as i walk, rolls down the window and they start yelling vulgar and sexual shit at me. i panic and time literally is going in slow motion as i reach into my handbag, grab the contents of an entire box of tampons, and throw it through the window of the car and all over the driver’s lap. the car stops moving and i hear a very loud “what the actual fuck” from one of the passengers. then i sprint off because i was slightly concerned for my own safety. but the look on the guys faces was literally the funniest thing i’d ever seen.
.
.
.

text:

text:
i forgive you, not because you deserve it, but because i do. as long as i hate you for what you did to me, as long as i loathe you for what you stole from me, you have power over me. you’ve taken so much life from me already, and while i’ve made the best of horrifying circumstances, i can’t allow you to have more. it’s been five harrowing years. “you can’t catch what’s coming to you with a closed hand,” and for the past two weeks, my fists and jaw have been clenched with anxiety about this anniversary. but this is where i leave your violence behind because my life is so full of wonder and i need to open myself to all of the laughter, joy, love, and possibility that it offers me.

i release you. i forgive you.

#believesurvivors

#wecanendrape

text:
while others gravitate to the kardashians  to emulate....as women we need to dig deeper than the exterior. 
the andrea constands, emily spantons, malala yousafzai's of our world are ones we should model after. these women have risen above all odds, against doubt, fought for what was right. they didn't stay down....they got up....they reached for the sky.... put their hands up high!
that's the kind of strength and leadership i want to follow and for my childrens future.

text:
🌺 what does “retreat” really mean?  here are some descriptions …
✨
💜 an act or process of withdrawing especially from what is difficult, dangerous, or disagreeable
💜 the process of receding from a position or state attained
💜 a place of privacy or safety or refuge
💜 a period of group withdrawal for prayer, meditation, study, or instruction under a director
✨
so, like an arrow which is drawn back first before being released, our retreat offers time to withdraw, consolidate and re-emerge with renewed clarity and energy and power.
🌺 
our next retreat in may 2019 welcomes stunning presenters from australian state & territories, plus goodie bags & raffles, sacred ceremonies, musical troubadour by the bonfire, organic vegan catering, yoga, meditation, tribal drumming, extreme warrior leap of faith from towering heights, archery, and so much more 😲 ✨
accommodation is comfortable and convenient - beds 🛏️ and bathrooms 🛀 (linen not included).
✨
we welcome you to join with us on the journey from the conception and the dreaming of this event to the creation, bubbling and then all the way to the climax and delivery so that you can become an integral part of the weaving and manifestation of this incredible vision!
✨
it is our hope that over the next months we can all begin to form some deep and true connections via this platform (check back here often for updates).
✨
in the sharing of this vision, we hope you will experience a sense of complete belonging, involvement and recognition as to what's in store for the vision for our bslr 2019: invoking the warrior woman retreat
✨
🎟️the early bird ticket deadline has been extended to 10 feb! save 25% 🎟️
✨
we also have payment plans available. see our website for more info (link in bio)
✨
red tent australia is a kind, caring, supporting, national, non-profit, social enterprise.
✨
our regular #retreats offer #yoga #meditation #palm readings #reflexology #tarot #aromatherapy facials #remedial massage #sound chime relaxation #reiki #bonfire #dancing. 🌺
#womensretreats  #healingretreats #invokingthewarriorwoman2019 #boundlessselfloveretreat #acceptance #belonging #community #womenscircles #bslr2019 #redtentau  #metoo

text:
first essay in our #metoo series. 
how photographer mahesh shantaram got away with #metoo⁠ ⁠ “shantaram begins his facebook post by vehemently declaring his liberal, feminist credentials. even shantaram’s instagram page carries the slogan “fuck patriarchy,” although it isn’t quite clear how he intends or proposes to do that given that his career is largely based on the photographing of that most patriarchal of social institutions, the heterosexual marriage. he insists that he has “been a vocal upholder of feminist causes and a fighter of the good fight” but no evidence of this claim is offered or available for us to see. he goes on to argue, “i know that no means no, and i know to take no for an answer,” echoing the now popular “no means no” slogan associated with anti-rape movements.

so why does he begin here? he wants the reader to know that he is a man who is incapable of doing what the women have accused him of doing. these assertions of feminist warrior-hood and of knowing when no means no assume that those who fight the feminist fight cannot be sexual harassers or those who stand with feminists cannot be abusers or those who “fight the good fight” cannot be predators.” by @suchitravijayan . read&share! @project_polis, @indiametoo, #art, #photography, #india, #timesup
https://www.thepolisproject.com/how-an-artist-gets-away-with-metoo-autopsy-of-an-apology/
name: THE POLIS PROJECT, Inc

first essay in our #metoo series. 
how photographer mahesh shantaram got away with #metoo⁠ ⁠ “shantaram begins his facebook post by vehemently declaring his liberal, feminist credentials. even shantaram’s instagram page carries the slogan “fuck patriarchy,” although it isn’t quite clear how he intends or proposes to do that given that his career is largely based on the photographing of that most patriarchal of social institutions, the heterosexual marriage. he insists that he has “been a vocal upholder of feminist causes and a fighter of the good fight” but no evidence of this claim is offered or available for us to see. he goes on to argue, “i know that no means no, and i know to take no for an answer,” echoing the now popular “no means no” slogan associated with anti-rape movements.

so why does he begin here? he wants the reader to know that he is a man who is incapable of doing what the women have accused him of doing. these assertions of feminist warrior-hood and of knowing when no means no assume that those who fight the feminist fight cannot be sexual harassers or those who stand with feminists cannot be abusers or those who “fight the good fight” cannot be predators.” by @suchitravijayan . read&share! @project_polis, @indiametoo, #art, #photography, #india, #timesup
https://www.thepolisproject.com/how-an-artist-gets-away-with-metoo-autopsy-of-an-apology/

text:
february is teen dating violence awareness month... and an alarming 1 in 3 teens will experience an abusive relationship. really think about that number for a minute.

few people realize that teens and young adults experience dating violence and sexual assault at higher rates than any other demographic.

these aren’t just statistics that happen in faraway places. dating abuse happens in every community. i know this because i experienced it as a teen, and because i receive countless disclosures from students every time i speak.

share this post to help spread the word, break the silence, and be part of the change.
.
.
.
#youthspeaker #preventioneducator #survivor #leadthechange 🎙💜✊🏼

text:
i am a survivor of childhood sexual abuse. that’s right, i’m a survivor, not a victim. 
in the years that i’ve been working through the trauma i have been able to overcome an eating disorder, genuinely forgive my abuser, work with police to file reports, and become an active participant in a wonderful grace-filled life. 
an important thing i remind myself is that healing begins once you feel heard. helplessness and isolation are the core experiences of trauma, but power and connection are the core experiences of recovery. so i suggest joining a support group, checking out what is available around you for talking, blogging, writing, connecting your experience to those of others. talk therapy has helped me tremendously. to be able to sit in a room and have someone listen to me and stay by my side has made such a difference. 
i was able to live again in the present moment by learning what i owned in the aftermath of the trauma. no amount of therapy or medication is ever going to stop our struggles if we don’t give ourselves permission to stop seeing ourselves as damaged goods and instead embrace the strength it took to make it through all our trauma, abuse, and neglect.

in the pursuit of health, i began making connections with healthy people. i became more self-aware and self-accountable.  i developed coping skills to help in the moments when i didn’t feel great. ultimately, i gained freedom and power in my life again. i remember when i was complaining about my job in one of my sessions, i said to my therapist… “oh my gosh, this is a normal person problem!” and i’ve had a lot more “normal” person problems. 
no matter your situation, i pray that you can find freedom inspiration from my testimony and continue to push and grow into all you were created to be. 
#ptsdrecovery #ptsd #recovery #eatingdisorder #eatingdisorderrecovery #anorexiarecovery #anorexia #posttraumaticgrowth #childhoodsecualassault #childhoodtrauma #metoo

if you’re a christian woman who wants help, prayer, guidance, encouragement, and a listening ear, please considering joining the bible thinking woman’s private facebook group👇🏽
support for sexually abused christian women. 
direct link is www.facebook.com/groups/hopeandhelpforsaints

text_retweet:
reposted from @muslimahnewsid - / perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks /
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.”
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
“menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
——

text:
era honesta por echar a volar en la dirección que quisiera haciendo caso omiso de la dirección del viento. ella era fuerte como el roble que no se parte, porque sabía echar raices allí dónde realmente encontraba el valor de la vida. tal y como lo correcto se siente, el daño se olvida. y quedaban sus valores, y su fe. quedaba recoger todo lo que era y ya no volvería a ser más. porque ahora sola se recogía. 
tenia la fe del ganador, y una mente tan grande que no cualquiera podía amedrentar. ella era mujer, de las que vió pura realidad sesgada, puro teatro organizado de vida. ella era mujer sentida del dolor de abajo, y reina del valor que sólo la elegancia del corazón és capaz de dar. ella era musa de su propio bienestar.

mujeres del mundo que se rebelaron e iluminaron a las demás. #juntaspodemosmais

text:
☝ crítica a mi 5ª novela: "hola, que le he dado a 'me gusta' y que sigo siendo fan. estoy leyendo la maga y me gusta tu escritura y los detalles como mensajes y demás en códigos coloquiales que sorprenden al releerlos. gracias margarita por esos murales de literatura para poder vivir en inocencia y en sabiduría del pueblo." :) (m. m.) 🍀 👋😹👍🐩💫puedes leer artículos míos en el apartado "colaboradores" de diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa), revista one stop y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🎶🦄💰💂 📚mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde: nimy novels arrive everywhere from
http://www.bubok.es/autores/bokusu
pincha el enlace en mi perfil.

verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores🔞you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults ✌😘✊ todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻

puedes seguirme además en youtube, fb (2 perfiles, uno más usado que el otro, y una página de autora), en twitter y soundcloud 🎤(otros 2 perfiles, uno de ellos con más de 30 grabaciones en español, inglés y francés macarrónico)📲 💃

text:
the month of me has begun...in 21 short days my personal new year will begin. so proud of the person i have become. i have taken ownership of my truths and i have remained unapologetic about them. as chapter 12 of book 39 comes to a close, i am happy. wow, to say that with all the ups and downs, throughout book 39 in my series called life, means a lot. i've taken financial hits, learned that some people in my circle didn't belong, continue to fight my anxieties, including my ptsd, and refuse to stop fighting, acknowledged that i am misunderstood by many and that's ok, and to top it all off i finally opened up to my mommy about a lot of things that i kept hidden. i feel free! more free than i've ever felt. i look foward to these days of reflection as my year comes to an end.

text:
the awareness and treatment for common mental illnesses such as depression, anxiety, and eating disorders has improved immeasurably in the past few hundred years. at the time of publication of lewis carroll’s alice’s adventures in wonderland, mental health was still a fairly remote topic. many of those who struggled with mental illness were simply classified as “mad” and put in an asylum or hidden from the public eye by their families, as mental illness was generally viewed as a “descent journey into a dark, subterraneous realm…” (falconer 12). “we’re all mad here” is one if the most quoted lines from lewis carroll’s alice’s adventures in wonderland. this line, spoken by the cheshire cat, does indeed reflect many aspects of the story well. when characters such as alice, the mad hatter, and the queen of hearts are looked at individually, they all display clear traits of various mental illnesses. this article will examine the extent to which lewis carroll gave the characters in alice’s adventures in wonderland and through the looking glass mental illnesses, and the possible biographical and historical reasons that carroll had for doing so.

text:
おはよう
たとえ、誰が何を言ってたとしても、あなたのペースでいい。あなたの選択でいい。誰かの為に生きてるんじゃない。自分自身の為に生きてる。

even if someone is saying something to you, keeping your pace is great and it’s great to act with your choice. we are not living for anyone. i live for myself.

#metoo #remetoo #praisethebrave 
#bubbleoff

text:
eartha kitt on love & compromise🥀 “i fall in love with myself, and i want someone to share it with me”

exercising compromise and self worth is a balancing act. especially for the black women, who have been history’s caregivers (often because of circumstance more than choice) there is a fine line between compromise and sacrifice that easily blurs so much that we find ourselves impeding on our sacred space to make things work. the trick is to maintain healthy compromise in our relationships (romantic, or not) while staying true to the boundaries that protect our sacred space.

text:
________________________________________доверие уходит по-английски. 
его теряют раз и навсегда. 
уходит - и ему не возвратиться 
ни через месяц, ни через года. 
доверие уходит не прощаясь, 
в душе лишь оставляя пустоту. 
порой кусок из сердца вырывая, 
похоронив надежду и мечту. 
оно с собой твою уносит веру 
в того, кого любил и уважал, 
взамен тебе оставив боль без меры, 
потери горечь и в спине - кинжал. 
и те, кто у тебя его ворует, 
живут-не тужат, совесть их не ест. 
но для тебя - уже не существуют. 
осталась только память - словно крест. …пусть эта боль тебя не убивает, 
хоть и земля уходит из-под ног. 
ты знай - намного больше тот теряет, 
кто растоптать твоё доверье смог!
забавина арина. 
#психология #psychology #психологическаяпомощь #psychological_hрelp
#притча##праздник #счастье#любовь#семья #мысли#философия #высказывания#печаль #грусть#psyxogram#love #cool#metoo#доброеутро

text:
the impact of #metoo on biglaw lateral partner moves
#
firms will increasingly be asking about harassment claims in their lateral partner forms. it’s a tricky thing, but it’s something you want to contain and deal with in a private way. — natasha innocenti, recruiter and partner at mlegal group inc., on how biglaw firms are dealing with the risk of a sexual harassment scandal in their lateral hires. she also notes that how a firm handles these issues matter to lateral candidates as well, “i do have candidates ask me all the time—men and women—is this firm good for women? that is a difference maker.” original article source...

text:
☝ crítica a mi 5ª novela: "hola, que le he dado a 'me gusta' y que sigo siendo fan. estoy leyendo la maga y me gusta tu escritura y los detalles como mensajes y demás en códigos coloquiales que sorprenden al releerlos. gracias margarita por esos murales de literatura para poder vivir en inocencia y en sabiduría del pueblo." :) (m. m.) 🍀 👋😹👍🐩💫puedes leer artículos míos en el apartado "colaboradores" de diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa), revista one stop y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🎶🦄💰💂 📚mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde: nimy novels arrive everywhere from
http://www.bubok.es/autores/bokusu
pincha el enlace en mi perfil.

verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores🔞you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults ✌😘✊ todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻

puedes seguirme además en youtube, fb (2 perfiles, uno más usado que el otro, y una página de autora), en twitter y soundcloud 🎤(otros 2 perfiles, uno de ellos con más de 30 grabaciones en español, inglés y francés macarrónico)📲 💃

text_retweet:
get to know this wonderful woman in about 45 mins on our facebook live @pageantrynow #repost @pageantrynow with @get_repost
・・・
this beauty will be on our show on feb 1 at 8pm et on our facebook live #repost @missnewfoundlandlabradorworld with @get_repost
・・・
as miss newfoundland and labrador world 2019, and hopefully as the next miss world canada, i want to highlight issues facing women today, especially issues surrounding sexual and domestic violence. when i was competing in miss teenage canada, i was in a not-so-great relationship. it was abusive. and part of the reason i stayed for so long was because i felt like i didn’t deserve any better. then, i spent a week in toronto with a group of incredibly talented and accomplished young women and realized my own worth, and gained the confidence to get out of the unhealthy relationship i was in. miss teenage canada saved me from having a life i never would have wanted. i found something i loved doing that made me happy and confident again, so i’m really excited to be representing my province nationally once again, this time at miss world canada. i just wanted to share my story to let other women know that if you’re in an unhealthy, abusive relationship, that you deserve better and you’re worthy of something better.  sharing this on instagram is kind of scary, and i wrote a blog post about it on my website (which was a little less scary because it has a much smaller following), but i just want other women to know that they’re not alone in these experiences and i hope this might inspire someone who’s struggling right now to leave if they’re in a bad situation. 
the number to the @nlsacpc should anyone need a 24/7 crisis and support line is 709-747-7757 .

text:
podría ser cualquiera de nosotras. quiéreme bien es cruda, real y triste. fue una de mis últimas lecturas del 2018, justo para el #guadalupereinas2018 y quede con un nudito en la garganta. si lo ven e librerías, no duden a darle una checada y llevárselo a casa. la historia va de rosalind (es una autobiografía) cuando conoció a brian (el brayan), un tío viudo con cuatro hijos, al inicio todo era bonito pero con el tiempo él comenzó a mostrar su lado oscuro, tóxico, peligroso. y ella no quiso salir de ahí, hasta que tocó fondo. si conocen a alguien que este pasando por una relación violenta podrían mostrárselo, quizá los ayude un poquito. .
.
.
.
las dos últimas semanas estuve de vacaciones y apenas leí por andar de marmota 🤭 e iba a subir este post con un mensaje bonito pero instagram me odió por dejarlo en borrador y no me dejó subirlo ☹️ igual se me vienen semanitas pesadas, a ver si me pongo más pilas en leer poquito diario y actualizar este insta que lo tengo olvidado 🤭 .
.
.

text:
“i’m gay, but most of the time when i go to the doctor they think i’m straight. nobody asks about my sexuality and that can be difficult to get good care. when i was growing up, nobody talked to me about sexual relationships with the same gender.  nobody ever addressed that in any of my classes, that was disappointing because when you’re growing up and part of the lgbtq community — even if you don’t know it yet— that can be really hard. you think it’s not an option and you don’t really know how to protect yourself adequately. for a lot of the lgbtq community, going to a healthcare provider can be tricky and unexpected obstacles can come up. but on of the things i noticed about planned parenthood was how inclusive everyone is in terms of acknowledging heteronormativity. what i really love about planned parenthood is that i’ve always  felt welcome and acknowledged and not just tolerated, but celebrated. “
•
@_mollyyyyyy •

#everyonehasavoice #worktogether
#weallmatter #hearmystory
#mystorymatters #loveyourself

#nobodycanchangeus #wearestrong
#weareunbreakable

“i’m gay, but most of the time when i go to the doctor they think i’m straight. nobody asks about my sexuality and that can be difficult to get good care. when i was growing up, nobody talked to me about sexual relationships with the same gender.  nobody ever addressed that in any of my classes, that was disappointing because when you’re growing up and pa of the lgbtq community — even if you don’t know it yet— that can be really hard. you think it’s not an option and you don’t really know how to protect yourself adequately. for a lot of the lgbtq community, going to a healthcare provider can be tricky and unexpected obstacles can come up. but on of the things i noticed about planned parenthood was how inclusive everyone is in terms of acknowledging heteronormativity. what i really love about planned parenthood is that i’ve always  felt welcome and acknowledged and not just tolerated, but celebrated. “

text:
/ perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks /
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.”
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
“menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
——
follow @muslimahnewsid
.

#khilafahajaranislam 
#selamatkanperempuan
#tolakruupks 
#islamsolusinegeri

it's #blackhistorymonth and my birthday month. join me on the journey of learning about people throughout history that i draw on my commute on the bus to work. i'm drawing @taranajaneen for day 1 of my #blackhistory drawings. 
tarana burke is a black civil rights activist from the bronx, new york who founded the me too movement. in 2006, burke began using the phrase "me too" to raise awareness of the pervasiveness of sexual abuse and assault in society, and the phrase developed into a broader movement, following the 2017 use of #metoo as a hashtag following the harvey weinstein sexual abuse allegations. (source: wikipedia)

text:

🗣|the victims|...
while human trafficking spans all demographics, there are some circumstances or vulnerabilities that lead to higher susceptibility to victimization and human trafficking. ➡️another reminder for why mindset is so critical to reducing our risk  toward violence and abuse. •
•who: runaway & homeless youth, as well as victims of domestic violence are often targeted by traffickers aka rapists/pedophiles. •
frequently lured by false promises of lucrative job, stability, education, or loving relationship. •
men, women, children, adults, foreign nationals or citizens. they all have diverse ethnic and socio-economic backgrounds, varied levels of education, and may be documented or not... and all share the trait of vulnerability. the sex traffickers manipulate and exploit these vulnerabilities to force labor and create dependency. ➡️victims can be divided into 3 categories 
1) children under 18 introduced into commercial sex
2) adults 18+ introduced into commercial sex through force, fraud, or coercion. 
3) children & adults introduced to perform labor or services through force, fraud, or coercion

text:
this new piece began as an exploration of intertextuality. i had been reflecting upon our current political climate, the “me too” movement, and feminist theory, when conceptualizing this satirical body of work. i found that behrpaint blues and greens are often labeled after natural elements, wether it’s sky blue, or forest green, or sage; where as the red’s and pinks are centralized around the female trope and gender roles that are exacerbated in our society such as drama queen, flirt alert, and shy smile. i combined the names that behrpaint paint uses to label their colors, with portraits of men that have abused their power, taken advantage of women, or have made misogynist/sexist remarks.

name of behr colors used for each unportrait from left to right:
1. "juicy details and innocent white" - kavanaugh 
2. "vixen and stolen kiss" - al franken 
3. "shy smile and angelic white" - pence
4. "glitterati and hushed white" - weinstein
5. "drama queen and powdered peach" - trump
6. "rule breaker and all made up" - acosta
7. "stiletto love and piggy bank" - mnuchin
8. "diva glam and high maintenance" - graham 
9. "youth blush and rumors" - epstein
10. "flirt alert and shady white" - clinton
11. "forbidden red and little princess" - weiner
12. "girls only" - blank pink canvas #girlsonly #believesurvivors #timesup #metoo #femaletrope #misogyny #stereotype #conceptualart #portraiture #painting #housepaint #behrpaint #art #artistic #portraitoftheday #loosebrushstrokes #paint #color #red #metoomovement #politicalart #callforchange #portrait #popart #quicksketch #polisci #resist #satire #genderroles #feminsttheory

text:
this new piece began as an exploration of intertextuality. i had been reflecting upon our current political climate, the “me too” movement, and feminist theory, when conceptualizing this satirical body of work. i found that behrpaint blues and greens are often labeled after natural elements, wether it’s sky blue, or forest green, or sage; where as the red’s and pinks are centralized around the female trope and gender roles that are exacerbated in our society such as drama queen, flirt alert, and shy smile. i combined the names that behrpaint paint uses to label their colors, with portraits of men that have abused their power, taken advantage of women, or have made misogynist/sexist remarks.

name of behr colors used for each unportrait from left to right:
1. "juicy details and innocent white" - kavanaugh 
2. "vixen and stolen kiss" - al franken 
3. "shy smile and angelic white" - pence
4. "glitterati and hushed white" - weinstein
5. "drama queen and powdered peach" - trump
6. "rule breaker and all made up" - acosta
7. "stiletto love and piggy bank" - mnuchin
8. "diva glam and high maintenance" - graham 
9. "youth blush and rumors" - epstein
10. "flirt alert and shady white" - clinton
11. "forbidden red and little princess" - weiner
12. "girls only" - blank pink canvas #girlsonly #believesurvivors #timesup #metoo #femaletrope #misogyny #stereotype #conceptualart #portraiture #painting #housepaint #behrpaint #art #artistic #portraitoftheday #loosebrushstrokes #paint #color #red #metoomovement #politicalart #callforchange #portrait #popart #quicksketch #polisci #resist #satire #genderroles #feminsttheory

text:
episode 14 of shit platypus says is available on @applepodcasts and @soundcloud:

on this episode we have a report on the yellow vest protests with our members ciat and teo, both currently in paris. they share their reflections on the mass demonstrations, the on-going crisis of neoliberalism and the confused responses by the left. after, yours hosts, laurie, suzy and pam talk about the memory of the 2008 financial crisis in popular culture and discuss some of the changes they foresee for labor and capital relations in the coming years. finally, if you still don't know what happened in 2008, let our resident financial genius, wentai, break it down for you at the end of our episode.

questions, suggestions and smart-ass commentary always welcome! e-mail us at shitplatypussays@gmail.com

hosted by pamela nogales, laurie rojas & suzy vogenthaler.

#capitalism #france #theleft #marxism #metoo #neoliberalism #paris #protest #socialism #yellowvests

text:
this is something that i don’t normally talk about. especially on social media- but i honestly feel like the experiences that we all have are not only for our benefit..but for others as well. i have been through hard things. (like many of you have) but because of those hard things- i’m able to relate and help others. i think that’s what god intended. 
so, my love life. haha

my love life sucked before i met tyler. it was so hard because i found myself dating people who treated me like garbage. ugh, don’t you hate that? everyone should be treated with love & kindness. no matter who you are. 
anyway- i dated people who were wonderful at first but then changed and i was taken advantage of. i dated people who were emotionally abusive. i had experiences where i was treated like an object, and then play those “mind games” like where they ghost you & don’t speak to you for a month...and then act like that never happened..!!
oh, and it gets worse...it got to the point where i was sexually harassed in college. i met someone nice and we worked together and i quickly saw that his intentions were not good. (i was scared to join in on the #metoo thing that happened a while ago. i give all the girls who were vulnerable and shared their stories massive props. it helped me understand that i wasn’t the only one) 
holy crap was that was so hard.
and i never thought i’d be good enough to find and marry someone wonderful. i felt like bc i was viewed & treated like garbage...i started to believe that i was..
gosh, dating was the worst. my self confidence was lower than rock bottom. 
but then, i served a mission. and for the first time in my whole life...for the first time i finally understood my self worth. 
i found myself. i learned that i am a daughter of god. and he loves me. and he wants the best for me always. i came home with super high expectations and would not give anyone the time of day if they didn’t treat me like i should be treated. no games. it was not a game to me. 
and then.. this super dashing, really really kind, most wonderful man on the planet walked into my life. my sweet husband, tyler. he treats me like a queen every single day.
*read the rest in the comments

text:
#day1 #lovingme2019 listening to motivational speeches have helped me so much in my life! i love starting my day with one. either while taking a shower, getting ready, or during my morning drive. it always makes me feel excited and like i can do anything. i hope you will feel the same way. this is one of my favorites and a go to when i need a pick me up. honestly so many are my favorites, but this was the first one that was introduced to me when i needed it most so i guess it has a certain comfort and reminder for me. what i usually do is go to youtube and search for morning motivation or motivational speeches and i just listen. if you have any favorites please share it below or send me a message, i'd love to hear it!! .
.
.
.
.
.

text:
ключові тренди 2019 складні і самодостатні. їх можна носити як самостійно, так і змішувати між собою в будь-яких пропорціях. головне – мода цього сезону поважає небанальні поєднання і змінені пропорції тіла. ♥️анімалістичний принт
в 2019 нікуди не сховатися від великої кількості анімалістичних принтів. мальовничі плями шкур леопарда, оцелота, зебри і тигра густо покрили подіуми чотирьох головних модних столиць світу. особливо ефектний вигляд матимуть нетрадиційні колірні поєднання "хижих" забарвлень з рожевим, малиновим або червоним.
♥️логотипи
розпочата кілька сезонів тому лихоманка під назвою "логоманія" в новому сезоні зменшувати обертів не планує. не залишилися до неї байдужі цього сезону навіть такі стійкі до масових тенденцій бренди як max mara і prada.
♥️кейпи
loewe, saint laurent, isabel marant і missoni знають толк в правильному верхньому одязі на осінь. вузькі пальта і піджаки, немов зняті з чоловічого плеча, змінюють просторі і розкішні кейпи. знову одяг супергероїв, оперних співаків і ченців-капуцинів справно слугуватиме на модній службі.
♥️багатошаровість
багатошаровість не можна назвати чистим трендом цієї весни. в плавний перехід від зими до весни, вбрання починають сповзатися в один великий текстильний "пиріг". головна відмінність цього сезону – "найсмачніші" поєднання фактур. нейлон з хутром або шерстю, оксамитом чи шкірою.
♥️сукня зі шкіри
шкіряні вбрання в епоху #metoo схожі на справжні модні лати і уніформу розгніваних домінатрікс. на поясі чи ні, довгі або мінімально короткі, похмуро чорні або життєрадісно помаранчеві – без них модний пазл цієї весни не складеться.
♥️срібло
вбрання в монолуках під кодовою назвою all in silver зроблять їх володарку схожою на стрімку срібну кулю, на дівчину з футуристичних 1960-х або на головну діву танцполу з вісімдесятих.
♥️плісирування
дрібне і ніжне плісирування на сукнях і спідницях затремтіло першим березневим теплом. носити їх будемо з брюками як у valentino, двоколірними гетрами sacai або пухнастими мохеровими светрами як у balenciaga. плісирування – найлегший і витончений тренд сезону.
продовження⬇️⬇️⬇️
name: СТУДІЯ ГАРНОГО ОДЯГУ🌺

тому лихоманка під назвою  логоманія  в новому сезоні зменшувати обертів не планує . не залишилися до неї байдужі цього сезону навіть такі стійкі до масових тенденцій бренди як max mara і prada . ♥️кейпи loewe , saint laurent , isabel marant і missoni знають толк в правильному верхньому одязі на осінь . вузькі пальта і піджаки , немов зняті з чоловічого плеча , змінюють просторі і розкішні кейпи . знову одяг супергероїв , оперних співаків і ченців-капуцинів справно слугуватиме на модній службі . ♥️багатошаровість багатошаровість не можна назвати чистим трендом цієї весни . в плавний перехід від зими до весни , вбрання починають сповзатися в один великий текстильний  пиріг  . головна відмінність цього сезону –  найсмачніші  поєднання фактур . нейлон з хутром або шерстю , оксамитом чи шкірою . ♥️сукня зі шкіри шкіряні вбрання в епоху схожі на справжні модні лати і уніформу розгніваних домінатрікс . на поясі чи ні , довгі або мінімально короткі , похмуро чорні або життєрадісно помаранчеві – без них модний пазл цієї весни не складеться . ♥️срібло вбрання в монолуках під кодовою назвою silver зроблять їх володарку схожою на стрімку срібну кулю , на дівчину з футуристичних 1960-х або на головну діву танцполу з вісімдесятих . ♥️плісирування дрібне і ніжне плісирування на сукнях і спідницях затремтіло першим березневим теплом . носити їх будемо з брюками як у valentino , двоколірними гетрами sacai або пухнастими мохеровими светрами як у balenciaga . плісирування – найлегший і витончений тренд сезону . продовження⬇️⬇️⬇️

text: 5/26: “i’m a 21 year old female who is graduating @uccs in less than 4 months with a bachelors in criminal justice, i work 2 jobs, & volunteer for el paso county’s correctional panel. outside of working hard, focusing on my goals, & bettering my day to day, i fit a social life in! honestly, i had to google dictionary the definition of “feminism” before i started to put my thoughts down because i hadn’t thought about it & my part i play in it. so here it is. i work hard, i’m determined, & i flourish in the environment i work/hang out in. i’m around hard working people, meaning all genders, sexes, & ages. these people i’m around are nursing students, managers, etc., trying to be the best they can be. i surround myself with people who have a passion for life, their job, their family & for themselves. i can sit here and say why i deserve to be “equal” to men, but i’m not. being equal & having a fair chance at something are two different things. to have a fair chance at a high position in a job, to have a fair chance in working more hours & making more money, to have a fair chance to explain why my opinion is as important as a males opinion. we can say equality is wanted between men & woman in jobs, the economy, our opinions. but i think if there is a fairness, that we can receive the same a man can, then it’s enough. if i work harder than a man, show more knowledge than a man, if you were to choose a man over me because he is male, that is your choice, & your loss. making a choice off the mere word of she’s “female” don’t hire her. she’s “female” don’t listen to her. it’s you’re loss. if a man is above me in what an employer wants, take him. but not just cause he’s a “man”. sex is simply a characteristic of our existence. if we were to make this characteristic a factor in our society, we are limiting brain power & strength we could have as a whole society. isn’t that what we wanted this whole time? peace? “equality”? i’m a hard working female who has shocked family, friends, myself even. who are any of you to tell me i “cant” do something or that i’m incapable because i have a pair of titties, an ass, & i can make a baby? suck it boys, i create life, b***h.”
name: Hana Hahn

text: i am trying each day to be the better person that i can be. not for others but for me. i know what it’s like to disappoint yourself and that is something i never ever want to feel again. some fights i fought scared the crap out of me but i fought them, i got through it. i didn’t give up because i thought about the future, my future. and i wanted to be able to smile and be proud of myself. i wanted to give myself something concrete, strong and healthy. today i smiled and laughed but i cried and panicked. i was scared and petrified. i heard things i was afraid to hear, i said things i wasn’t ready to speak. but yet i found once more the strength to end this day with a smile on my face. no matter the amount of tear shed, the brightness of my smile tonight wipes them all. i once again rose up from today’s ashes. even if tomorrow scares me, i know i can do it. #keepsmiling #staystrong #youredoingamazingsweetie #youredoinggreat #keepyourgoals #beproudofyou #embraceyourself #bepositive #inspirationalquotes #inspiration #inspirational #inspirationalquotesandsayings #inspirationalthoughts #selfie #past #choseyourpath #metoo #ibelieveher

text:
🎞iniciativa // o @mulhernocinema (ótimo, por sinal) criou uma lista personalizada de dezenas de filmes dirigidos por mulheres para quem quer participar da campanha #52filmsbywomen, lançada pelo braço de los angeles da organização women in film and television, da qual já fazem parte mais de 10 mil pessoas. . 
a ideia é a seguinte: você apoia o mulher no cinema com r$ 20 por mês e recebe a lista de 52 de filmes dirigidos por mulheres, baseadas em suas preferências cinematográficas e nas diretoras que você quer conhecer (se houver). o valor também garante uma newsletter quinzenal com curadoria de conteúdo sobre mulheres no cinema e participe de sorteios regulares de livros, cartazes, ingressos e outros brindes. e você ainda ajuda o mulher no cinema a fazer uma cobertura cada vez melhor e mais relevante.
.
.
no site também é possível ver outras listas e críticas sobre o mesmo tema, inclusive indicações de obras disponíveis na netflix. para seguir e apoiar hoje.

it’s our birthday 🎂 *

all three of us will be celebrating a birthday within the first week of february. i used to make a huge deal about my birthday. even when i did something low key, it was a big deal to me!
*
once i realized the girls would be born pretty close to my birthday, they got the side eye 😒 however, i’m starting to look forward to these shared celebrations with them. they’ve changed my life for the better. it’s only fitting that we celebrate together ❤️❤️

text:
sabías que?!
los instructores de skydivefoz son profesionales con gran experiencia y años en el paracaidismo, que acumulan millares de saltos;
quincenalmente se practica el “día de la seguridad” o “safety day” como es conocido. consiste en un entrenamiento entre todos los involucrados en la operación sobre seguridad, procedimientos y los más relevantes asuntos que comprenden el paracaidismo nacional e internacional;
anualmente los instructores son sometidos a un conjunto de exámenes exigidos por la confederación brasileña de paracaidismo.
.

text: i feel this weight on my chest. i feel everything i go through must be expressed, i cannot let this settle in, find it's way and creep around my body. because it weighs me down. i feel every relationship i've been through, every person i've loved and lost, is a story that must be told. because i feel my life isn't happening for me or to me, it's happening for those around me. and if my life, my existence, isn't a lesson or an inspiration to others around me; if my struggle doesn't find another person and tuck them safely under their blanket, and make them feel they are not alone; if my life doesn't do this, it's not worth it. it's a pretty unrealistic thing to say, and i know it...and maybe somewhere along the way i may change, i might finally be able to love myself when i'm nothing to the people around me. but for now this is who i am.

text:
ich habe etwas veröffentlicht, dass mir sehr wichtig ist.
ich möchte nicht, dass dadurch mitleid oder aufmerksamkeit entsteht.
das möchte ich alles nicht.
ichh habe das veröffentlicht zum einen für mich ich habe es mir von der seele geschrieben, damit geht's mir besser und vielleicht kann ich so mit dem einen oder anderen menschen zeigen, dass egal was einem passiert ist man sich dafür nicht schämen muss, dass man sich nicht verstecken muss, dass man sich für nichts schämen muss was einem angetan wurde.
don't be ashamed of your story.
ich würde mich wirklich freuen, wenn ihr euch die zeit nehmt, euch das durchlest und naja ihr euch vielleicht eure gedanken darüber macht, zum einen falls unter euch ein täter ist, was ihr einem anderen menschen damit antut, wenn es ein "opfer" unter euch gibt, dass ihr euch nicht schämen müsste, dass ihr weiter machen müsste, dass ihr kämpfen müsst und, dass es sich lohnt, und dann all die leute die davon nicht betroffen sind, in keiner hinsicht, vielleicht könnt auch ihr euch eure gedanken machen.
menschen haben gründe  wieso sie angst haben oder wieso sie so, sind wie sie sind. 
ihr müsst die menschen akzeptieren wie sie sind, denn in den meisten fällen können sie nichts dafür, dass sie so sind wie sie sind.
sie wurden zu dem gemacht was sie sind.
wie gesagt, ich möchte damit weder irgendein mitleid bekommen ich möchte keine unnötige aufmerksamkeit damit.
ich möchte insofern aufmerksamkeit dafür, dass das ganze einfach kein tabuthema mehr ist, dass sich keiner schämt über so etwas zu reden, wenn es jemand passiert ist, dass er sich nicht versteckt, dass das man einfach zudem steht wer man ist und zu dem steht was einem passiert ist.
es ist nicht eure schuld wenn euch so etwas passiert ist.
steh zu euch selbst, ihr werdet stärker durch die dinge die euch passiert sind, kämpft um wieder nach oben zu kommen es lohnt sich, es lohnt sich wirklich.
es gibt da draußen immer menschen die zu 100% hinter euch stehen, die euch unterstützen und die für euch da sein sind.
ihr habt ihr eine familie die euch braucht und alleine dafür lohnt es sich zu kämpfen, sich aus dem loch zu kämpfen und wieder zurück ins leben zu finden.

brooklyn nine-nine star stephanie beatriz on directing #metoo episode
#
stephanie beatriz as rosa diaz in nbc’s brooklyn nine-nine. vivian zink/nbc throughout its two-network life span, brooklyn nine-nine has endeared itself to fans through charming characters, zany humor and running quirks and gags that make the little-watched but much-loved police comedy feel like an inside joke. while the series has proven capable of tugging on the heart strings and supplying a heaping helping of thematic storytelling, it has largely steered clear of more serious real-world issues that other sitcoms occasionally like to tee up.but that changes this season as stephanie beatriz—who plays the brilliantly dark detective rosa diaz—makes her directorial debut for an episode tackling the #metoo movement. in a recent interview with variety, beatriz discussed what her goal was in addressing a heavier topic in such a light-hearted series.subscribe to observer’s entertainment newsletter“especially in comedy, we need to focus down into what the moment is supposed to be and how truthful we can make it, and that is what i wanted to do on-set that week,” she said. “and particularly the scenes that were more emotional—there was a good chunk for melissa fumero [who plays sgt. amy santiago] that was painful because all of us have had an experience like that, that’s…

text:
i am so excited to announce that on february 20th, world day of social justice, i will release my newest single, ‘shine’!
•
i wrote ‘shine’ this past summer, when i was feeling particularly helpless in regards to the state my country is in. ‘shine’ acknowledges how small we all can feel in the universe, in our own homes, and in our own lives. but it is also an anthem to empower listeners to speak up and asks that we all continue to fight for what we believe.
•
✨keep on shining✨
.
.
.

text:
are you breaking your word if you speak out about your abuse? no. way.

this morning i was doing some thinking.

back in the day, i remember the international mission board telling me as long as i didn’t use their name, or the man’s name who abused me, then it would be okay to write about it and speak about it in my book and talks.

and when i read through the 300-page transcript of their interview with me during their investigation, they asked me if i was going to write about it or speak about it and i said no.

over the years, i’ve let the idea of “keeping my word” to them keep me silent. when people would ask about my abuse after i would speak or when they would read my book, i’d say i “legally” couldn’t say anything about it because i thought since i told them i wouldn’t, and it was recorded on paper, that i could get in trouble for talking about it. only my closest friends and family knew.

when i decided to come forward, i also read a part of the transcript that said i would talk about it if someone else came forward and i felt the need to. when i said it, i meant another victim of the man who abused me. but 12 years later, i feel like the #metoo and #churchtoo movements empowered me to speak.

so many times people have told me about their abuse and how they have been told to keep quiet. they’ve promised to not name their abuser, and they feel as if going against their word is a “sin” or doing something wrong.

keeping your word means doing what you’re going to say you’re going to do so that you will be a person of integrity. a person of integrity does what’s right to keep themselves and others around them whole, healthy, safe, and valued.

if you have promised someone you won’t speak out about the abuse that happened to you, or abuse that you know about, by talking about it, you are not breaking your word. you’re breaking the silence. you’re keeping your word to protect, honor, and value human life and dignity.

you are not “sinning.” you are not going against the truth. even though you may have told someone you’ll keep abuse a secret, you have the right (and often times the responsibility) to speak up. {{full post: link in profile}}

text: a strange part of homeschooling is how it invites some people to question your parental instincts. the choice of homeschooling is often misunderstood. but it’s what we’ve chosen for our family and it’s been good for us. it’s truly allowed me to have a better connection with my children and be able to guide my children as they explore the world around them. people might not understand the journey right now but they will soon. be bold in your homeschooling choices and make your child’s experience as memorable as you dreamed 🌈💖🙏🏾. if you’re new to homeschooling follow us and be apart of a growing community of women striving daily to give their child an educational experience that is designed just for them💖

text:
anyone with anxiety and depression knows how debilitating it can be, but by developing a state of self-reflection, vulnerability and an understanding of where you feel it in your body, we can begin to detach from the stigma and see yourself for who you really are.

this conversation based workshop will include eastern yogic philosophy, breath work, asana, chanting, meditation and journaling. a safe and sacred space will be provided as you are embraced by a loving and supportive community.

this 3 hour workshop is for all levels and will take you on a journey to explore ways to help soften and reduce the pressures of daily living as you work on creating inner peace. having a deep relationship and commitment to mental health awareness ashlee wanted develop a community to remind you that you are not alone and and that together we can reduce the stigmatization of mental illness.

dates:

february 17, 2019
march 24, 2019
april 21, 2019
may 19, 2019

name: Broken Drishti
tweet_full:
anyone with anxiety and depression knows how debilitating it can be, but by developing a state of self-reflection, vulnerability and an understanding of where you feel it in your body, we can begin to detach from the stigma and see yourself for who you really are.

this conversation based workshop will include eastern yogic philosophy, breath work, asana, chanting, meditation and journaling. a safe and sacred space will be provided as you are embraced by a loving and supportive community.

this 3 hour workshop is for all levels and will take you on a journey to explore ways to help soften and reduce the pressures of daily living as you work on creating inner peace. having a deep relationship and commitment to mental health awareness ashlee wanted develop a community to remind you that you are not alone and and that together we can reduce the stigmatization of mental illness.

text: the @womensmarch got me thinking a lot about representation and inclusivity. when i first made the bye patriarchy girl, i hoped her cartoon-color skin and giant hair would be neutral, generic enough for all girls to see themselves in her. i gave her rainbow hair for the march poster to expand her message. finally i had to admit that she had a long way to go to include all girls- she’s pretty white. i’ve been exploring skin color and hair texture/style, and it seems like she cant do it all on her own with a makeover - she needs her community. say hello to her first buddy, in a few color variations because we can have all the colors.  #blackhistorymonth #blackhistorymonth2019

text:
#fbf| jada pinkett-smith asked an important question several weeks ago when r. kelly’s music sales spiked after the documentary. ✨

why have his record sales continued to rise? and we would add, what does it say about how we view black women and girls who are survivors? ✨

tarana burke, @taranajaneen, who started the #metoo movement, and is herself a three-time survivor of childhood sexual abuse, writes for @the.root about how widespread this is in communities of color: ”native americans have the highest rate of sexual assault in the country with a probability that nearly 27 percent of native women will experience rape in their lifetimes. black women follow that with a probability of 22 percent—or 3,186,000 being raped over the span of their lives.” ✨ ✨ ✨ “according to preliminary findings by black women’s blueprint, “60% of black girls experience sexual assault… by the time they reach 18” (black women’s blueprint, n.d.)... ✨ source: american psychological association ✨

share your thoughts with us below. 👇🏾this needs to be an ongoing conversation! 🗣💜 we have to #breakthesilence so we can heal. ✨ ✨ peep our stories for a short clip from @yarimakarama about why #yoursilencewillnotprotectyou. ✨

turning pain into purpose ⠀
